 \sum_{k=0}^{n} \frac{1}{k+1} \binom{n}{k} 
\sum_{k=0} ^n \frac  1{k+1}\binom nk X^{k+1} 
f(X) =  \sum_{k=0} ^n \frac  1{k+1}\binom nk X^{k+1}\\ f'(X) =  \sum_{k=0} ^n \binom nk X^{k} = (1+X)^n\implies f(X) =  \frac1{n+1}(1+X)^{n+1} \\ \sum_{k=0} ^n \frac  1{k+1}\binom nk  = f(1)-f(0) = \frac{2^{n+1}-1}{n+1} 
\frac  1{k+1}\binom nk X^{k+1} = \frac {n!}{(n-k)! (k+1)!} = \frac1{n+1}\frac {(n+1)!}{(n-k)! (k+1)!}  = \frac1{n+1} \binom {n+1}{k+1} 
\sum_{k=0} ^n \frac  1{k+1}\binom nk =\frac1{n+1}\sum_{k=0} ^n \binom{n+1}{k+1} = \frac{2^{n+1}-1}{n+1} 
